# CODEOWNERS — control-plane lock (council fix, 2026-07-18)
#
# These paths are the "control plane": the CI that deploys, the engine that publishes,
# and the guardrail documents the caged worker reads at runtime. A change to any of them
# by the worker (or anyone) must be reviewed by the owner before it can merge — so a
# poisoned or hallucinated task can never quietly rewrite the rules or the publisher.
#
# ENFORCEMENT NOTE: this file only bites when the branch ruleset has
# "Require review from Code Owners" turned ON. That toggle is an owner action in
# GitHub → repo Settings → Rules/Branches. Until then this file is documentation.

# CI / deploy workflows — the AI must never be able to change how the site deploys.
/.github/                         @renielreyes

# The Command Center engine — the one program that holds every project's merge key.
/command-center/                  @renielreyes

# The runtime guardrails the worker is fed each build (charter + driver prompt).
/Infra/AI Executor Charter.md     @renielreyes
/Infra/driver-prompt.md           @renielreyes
